1
00:00:06,688 --> 00:00:09,768
- Dr. Al-Hashimi, you OK?

2
00:00:09,808 --> 00:00:12,728
- Did you ever notice anything
unusual about her behavior?

3
00:00:12,768 --> 00:00:14,288
- Um, this morning,

4
00:00:14,288 --> 00:00:16,368
when she was checking labs
on Baby Jane Doe,

5
00:00:16,408 --> 00:00:18,448
it was like she zoned out
for a few seconds.

6
00:00:18,488 --> 00:00:19,528
[cheers]

7
00:00:19,568 --> 00:00:20,528
- Hey.
- All right.

8
00:00:20,568 --> 00:00:21,528
- Not so fast.

9
00:00:21,568 --> 00:00:23,368
Every chart from
the last five hours

10
00:00:23,408 --> 00:00:25,568
needs to be scanned into
the electronic health record.

11
00:00:25,608 --> 00:00:26,648
- Are you kidding me?

12
00:00:26,688 --> 00:00:27,968
- That's gonna take forever.

13
00:00:28,008 --> 00:00:29,128
- Why are you jonesing
so hard to get out

14
00:00:29,168 --> 00:00:30,328
and start your ride tonight?

15
00:00:30,368 --> 00:00:32,208
- I just have to get going.

16
00:00:32,248 --> 00:00:33,968
- You stay,
and I'll get together

17
00:00:34,008 --> 00:00:35,448
everything you'll need at home.

18
00:00:36,568 --> 00:00:37,528
Orlando.

19
00:00:37,568 --> 00:00:38,808
Oh, my God.

20
00:00:38,848 --> 00:00:40,808
- You let him leave?

21
00:00:40,848 --> 00:00:42,048
- He knew the risks.

22
00:00:42,088 --> 00:00:43,848
We honored his decision
to leave.

23
00:00:43,848 --> 00:00:46,128
- Please, sign out all
this shit that's bugging you

24
00:00:46,168 --> 00:00:47,328
and get out of here.

25
00:00:47,368 --> 00:00:48,488
- I can't.

26
00:00:48,528 --> 00:00:50,528
- We'll all manage
until you come back.

27
00:00:50,568 --> 00:00:51,568
We always do.

28
00:00:51,608 --> 00:00:53,768
- Yeah, what if
I don't come back?

29
00:00:53,808 --> 00:00:56,168
[tense music]

30
00:01:07,648 --> 00:01:10,688
[indistinct chatter]

31
00:01:16,968 --> 00:01:18,768
- What's up, Ghost Rider?
- You good?

32
00:01:18,808 --> 00:01:19,928
- Never better.

33
00:01:19,968 --> 00:01:21,608
- OK, kids, bye-bye time.

34
00:01:21,648 --> 00:01:23,968
Thanks for the trip
down memory lane.

35
00:01:24,008 --> 00:01:25,328
Um, where's Evans?

36
00:01:25,328 --> 00:01:27,728
- Uh, I think
she's by the family room.

37
00:01:27,768 --> 00:01:29,208
- She is.

38
00:01:29,248 --> 00:01:30,608
- Hey, hey, hey,
where are you going?

39
00:01:30,648 --> 00:01:32,248
I'm not gonna scan
all this by myself.

40
00:01:32,288 --> 00:01:33,928
- Cruz has a question
on my cellulitis.

41
00:01:33,968 --> 00:01:35,408
I'll be right back.
- You better.

42
00:01:35,448 --> 00:01:36,808
- Two minutes tops.
- Where's Mel?

43
00:01:36,848 --> 00:01:38,208
Where's Donnie?

44
00:01:38,248 --> 00:01:39,808
They should be helping you.
- I don't know.

45
00:01:39,808 --> 00:01:41,408
- OK, day shift, listen up.

46
00:01:41,408 --> 00:01:43,488
We're doing really well,
but we still got a ways to go.

47
00:01:43,528 --> 00:01:45,808
And nobody's going home
until all these paper charts

48
00:01:45,848 --> 00:01:47,368
are digitized, including me.

49
00:01:47,408 --> 00:01:49,528
- And then we're free
to celebrate our freedom?

50
00:01:49,568 --> 00:01:50,408
- Exactly.

51
00:01:50,448 --> 00:01:51,808
- Well, can you kick some ass

52
00:01:51,848 --> 00:01:52,928
and get the staff to hurry up

53
00:01:52,968 --> 00:01:54,088
on the EHR home pages?

54
00:01:54,088 --> 00:01:55,848
- Where are Larry and Antoine?

55
00:01:55,888 --> 00:01:57,088
- Antoine's fighting
on the phone

56
00:01:57,088 --> 00:01:58,368
with his girlfriend outside.

57
00:01:58,408 --> 00:02:01,208
And Larry's on a cafeteria run.

58
00:02:01,248 --> 00:02:03,648
- Yeah, that tracks.

59
00:02:03,688 --> 00:02:05,768
- We've got five patients
in beds waiting to be seen.

60
00:02:05,768 --> 00:02:07,968
How do you want to play this--
man to man or zone?

61
00:02:07,968 --> 00:02:09,328
- The zone.

62
00:02:09,368 --> 00:02:11,048
Have Cruz and Ellis split up
the new five.

63
00:02:11,088 --> 00:02:12,368
You take North and Central.

64
00:02:12,408 --> 00:02:14,128
I'll take South and Trauma.
- Cool.

65
00:02:14,168 --> 00:02:15,408
Want to switch at 1:00 AM?

66
00:02:15,408 --> 00:02:16,288
- Why?

67
00:02:16,328 --> 00:02:17,448
- Variety is the spice of life.

68
00:02:17,488 --> 00:02:19,008
- I thought that was garlic.

69
00:02:19,048 --> 00:02:22,008
- Oh, sorry.

70
00:02:22,048 --> 00:02:23,928
[sighs]
I told you I'd be fast.

71
00:02:23,968 --> 00:02:26,008
OK, let's do this
and get out of here.

72
00:02:26,048 --> 00:02:27,088
- What's the hurry?

73
00:02:27,128 --> 00:02:28,488
Got some hay to pitch?

74
00:02:28,528 --> 00:02:29,848
- Ha.

75
00:02:29,888 --> 00:02:31,248
[bell chimes]

76
00:02:31,288 --> 00:02:33,048
Oh, shoot.
- What?

77
00:02:33,088 --> 00:02:35,528
- Uh, my ID badge is missing.

78
00:02:35,568 --> 00:02:36,768
- Oh, no.
The one you just got?

79
00:02:36,808 --> 00:02:38,088
How'd you lose it?

80
00:02:38,128 --> 00:02:39,088
- I don't know.
It must have come off.

81
00:02:39,128 --> 00:02:40,368
- Classic.

82
00:02:40,368 --> 00:02:41,848
Hope you remember
your login and password.

83
00:02:41,888 --> 00:02:42,968
- OK. Retrace your steps.

84
00:02:43,008 --> 00:02:44,368
Where'd you have it last?

85
00:02:44,368 --> 00:02:47,088
- Uh, I was with Ogilvie
in the Ambulance Bay.

86
00:02:47,128 --> 00:02:49,208
- Not with Colonel Mustard
in the library?

87
00:02:49,248 --> 00:02:51,448
- Who's--what?

88
00:02:51,488 --> 00:02:52,648
No.

89
00:02:53,888 --> 00:02:56,408
- The boy has no clue.

90
00:02:57,048 --> 00:03:00,488
[machine dinging]

91
00:03:00,488 --> 00:03:02,728
- Please don't do that.

92
00:03:02,768 --> 00:03:04,328
- Oh, ma'am, I gotta go.

93
00:03:04,368 --> 00:03:07,328
I sit here any longer,
I'm gonna get bedsores.

94
00:03:09,248 --> 00:03:12,208
I--I'm supposed to get
some CT results.

95
00:03:12,248 --> 00:03:14,768
Any idea how much longer
that's gonna be?

96
00:03:14,808 --> 00:03:17,168
- Shouldn't be much longer.

97
00:03:17,168 --> 00:03:19,808
- Where's that Nurse Vivi?

98
00:03:19,848 --> 00:03:21,408
- You don't want any of that.

99
00:03:21,408 --> 00:03:23,608
- No?
- No, she's out of your league.

100
00:03:23,608 --> 00:03:25,568
- What league do you think
I play in?

101
00:03:25,608 --> 00:03:28,408
- Uh, old timer's night.
- [laughs]

102
00:03:28,448 --> 00:03:29,928
Yeah, you're probably right.

103
00:03:29,968 --> 00:03:33,248
But some teams still appreciate
a veteran presence.

104
00:03:33,288 --> 00:03:35,408
- Well, don't say
I didn't warn you.

105
00:03:35,448 --> 00:03:37,208
You are here for your heart,
after all.

106
00:03:37,248 --> 00:03:38,808
- My heart's been
broken before.

107
00:03:38,848 --> 00:03:40,248
What's one more time?

108
00:03:40,288 --> 00:03:42,328
- Uh, she's engaged
to a jujitsu instructor.

109
00:03:42,328 --> 00:03:44,048
- With a bang,
not a whimper, baby.

110
00:03:44,088 --> 00:03:45,408
- [laughs]

111
00:03:45,448 --> 00:03:46,968
- And it's a cool bath
a couple times a day

112
00:03:46,968 --> 00:03:49,768
for two days, followed by
aloe vera to your skin.

113
00:03:49,808 --> 00:03:51,048
- OK, that's it?

114
00:03:51,088 --> 00:03:53,248
- And sunscreen in your future.

115
00:03:53,288 --> 00:03:56,248
- No, I'm never going outside
ever again.

116
00:03:56,288 --> 00:03:59,648
- I wouldn't swear off the sun
entirely, you know?

117
00:03:59,648 --> 00:04:02,248
But like most things,
moderation.

118
00:04:02,248 --> 00:04:03,448
- Hey, we're getting
kind of shorthanded

119
00:04:03,488 --> 00:04:04,768
scanning charts out here.

120
00:04:04,808 --> 00:04:06,288
When you finish,
can you come lend a hand?

121
00:04:06,288 --> 00:04:07,328
- Yeah, happy to.

122
00:04:07,368 --> 00:04:08,648
- Thank you.

123
00:04:10,408 --> 00:04:12,328
- And by happy to,
I mean there is nothing

124
00:04:12,368 --> 00:04:14,128
I would rather do less.

125
00:04:14,168 --> 00:04:16,648
- They keep you pretty busy.

126
00:04:16,688 --> 00:04:20,968
- Yeah, and today has brought
some new challenges.

127
00:04:20,968 --> 00:04:22,168
This is really putting a crimp

128
00:04:22,168 --> 00:04:24,368
in my 4th of July
evening plans.

129
00:04:24,408 --> 00:04:26,808
- You're going to see
the fireworks?

130
00:04:26,808 --> 00:04:30,328
- Uh, no, I was gonna maybe
meet up with this guy,

131
00:04:30,368 --> 00:04:32,008
though that's sounding
less appealing

132
00:04:32,048 --> 00:04:34,408
than the three Bs
at this point.

133
00:04:34,448 --> 00:04:36,328
- The three Bs?

134
00:04:37,088 --> 00:04:39,408
- Book, bath, and bed.

135
00:04:39,448 --> 00:04:41,968
- College kid with mono
and hemorrhagic tonsils,

136
00:04:42,008 --> 00:04:43,728
admit med-surge or observation?

137
00:04:43,768 --> 00:04:44,608
- Uh, observation.

138
00:04:44,648 --> 00:04:46,128
Bleeding stopped with TXA.

139
00:04:46,168 --> 00:04:47,488
She's had steroids,
so should be

140
00:04:47,528 --> 00:04:48,928
ready for discharge
in the morning.

141
00:04:48,968 --> 00:04:50,528
- Cool.

142
00:04:50,568 --> 00:04:52,368
How was your first shift back?

143
00:04:52,368 --> 00:04:55,088
- Uh, slow start,
finding my rhythm.

144
00:04:55,128 --> 00:04:56,288
- [chuckles]

145
00:04:56,328 --> 00:04:58,168
You a little rusty,
Rusty James?

146
00:04:58,168 --> 00:05:00,688
Now you won't have Motorcycle
Boy to big brother you.

147
00:05:00,728 --> 00:05:02,608
- Is that a "Rumble Fish"
reference?

148
00:05:02,608 --> 00:05:03,768
- Sure is.

149
00:05:03,808 --> 00:05:06,648
- And Robby is my big brother
in this analogy?

150
00:05:06,688 --> 00:05:07,648
- Bingo.

151
00:05:07,688 --> 00:05:08,968
- Yeah, I wouldn't say
he's been

152
00:05:09,008 --> 00:05:10,648
looking out for me exactly.

153
00:05:10,688 --> 00:05:12,248
I think he'd probably prefer

154
00:05:12,288 --> 00:05:13,808
not to see me at all
today, actually.

155
00:05:13,848 --> 00:05:16,728
- And you think that's
because he's mad at you?

156
00:05:16,768 --> 00:05:21,688
- I think he feels like
I let him down, because I did.

157
00:05:21,728 --> 00:05:23,808
- Jesus, with all
the martyrs around here,

158
00:05:23,848 --> 00:05:25,408
you'd think this was
a passion play.

159
00:05:25,448 --> 00:05:27,368
- What's your take?

160
00:05:29,168 --> 00:05:30,448
- I worked with that man
for 10 months

161
00:05:30,488 --> 00:05:31,808
while you were gone.

162
00:05:31,848 --> 00:05:33,408
He's not mad at you.

163
00:05:33,408 --> 00:05:36,728
He's mad at himself
for failing you, Rusty James.

164
00:05:36,768 --> 00:05:38,048
- Really?

165
00:05:38,088 --> 00:05:39,248
- [sighs]

166
00:05:39,288 --> 00:05:41,808
Just more
White Knight/White noise.

167
00:05:41,848 --> 00:05:43,448
That's how it is.

168
00:05:45,488 --> 00:05:47,168
- Share this video
with your friends if you can.

169
00:05:47,208 --> 00:05:48,448
Thank you so much.

170
00:05:48,488 --> 00:05:50,408
Be kind, be safe, be brave.

171
00:05:50,448 --> 00:05:51,488
- What you doing?

172
00:05:51,528 --> 00:05:53,048
- Dr. Robby, sorry.

173
00:05:53,088 --> 00:05:54,048
I was just--

174
00:05:54,088 --> 00:05:55,408
- One of your TikToks? Yeah.

175
00:05:55,448 --> 00:05:56,888
About those, listen,
I'm not so sure that--

176
00:05:56,928 --> 00:05:58,768
- No, no, I was just sharing--
- No, I get it.

177
00:05:58,768 --> 00:06:00,368
I just--you know,
we do have HIPAA laws here.

178
00:06:00,368 --> 00:06:01,888
We don't let anybody film--

179
00:06:01,928 --> 00:06:03,288
- I would never violate
any HIPAA laws, Dr. Robby.

180
00:06:03,328 --> 00:06:04,488
I swear it.
- I understand.

181
00:06:04,528 --> 00:06:05,488
Even still,
we're getting behind

182
00:06:05,528 --> 00:06:06,568
on scanning patient charts.

183
00:06:06,608 --> 00:06:07,568
So how about no TikTok

184
00:06:07,608 --> 00:06:10,448
on the company clock, Dr. J?

185
00:06:10,488 --> 00:06:12,408
- Dr. Robby, I think you're--

186
00:06:12,448 --> 00:06:13,768
- Out of touch? Probably.

187
00:06:13,808 --> 00:06:15,288
You wouldn't be the first
to accuse me of it.

188
00:06:15,328 --> 00:06:16,848
However, when I was
in medical school--

189
00:06:16,888 --> 00:06:18,768
- You didn't have cell phones
or TikTok

190
00:06:18,808 --> 00:06:21,408
or internet or ICE agents
coming in here

191
00:06:21,448 --> 00:06:23,968
and taking away patients
and staff.

192
00:06:25,808 --> 00:06:27,448
I get it.

193
00:06:30,928 --> 00:06:34,768
- We did have cell phones,
maybe not in the beginning.

194
00:06:39,248 --> 00:06:40,368
Where do you think
you're going?

195
00:06:40,408 --> 00:06:41,888
- Uh, home.

196
00:06:41,928 --> 00:06:44,168
- I kind of need you
to hang out a little longer

197
00:06:44,208 --> 00:06:46,288
and help digitize some of these
analog patient records.

198
00:06:46,328 --> 00:06:47,648
- Normally, I would, truly.

199
00:06:47,688 --> 00:06:51,968
But I gotta get home--
wife, baby, bed.

200
00:06:52,008 --> 00:06:53,888
- OK.
Go get some rest.

201
00:06:53,888 --> 00:06:55,208
You sure you're OK
to drive home?

202
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:56,208
- Absolutely.

203
00:06:56,248 --> 00:06:58,168
Just enough in the tank.

204
00:06:58,208 --> 00:07:00,248
- Don't tell anybody
I let you go.

205
00:07:00,288 --> 00:07:01,488
- Deal.

206
00:07:01,528 --> 00:07:02,888
Safe travels.

207
00:07:02,928 --> 00:07:05,128
Be sure to send some pictures
from the road.

208
00:07:21,808 --> 00:07:23,608
- Fight over at
Zazu's Sports Bar.

209
00:07:23,648 --> 00:07:25,128
The two combatants
are pulling up soon.

210
00:07:25,168 --> 00:07:26,328
One's a stabbing.

211
00:07:26,368 --> 00:07:27,328
- Ellis, double trauma
coming in.

212
00:07:27,368 --> 00:07:28,408
Grab the easy one.

213
00:07:28,448 --> 00:07:29,488
Bring the stabbing to Trauma 2.

214
00:07:29,528 --> 00:07:31,048
We will get the room set up.

215
00:07:31,088 --> 00:07:33,288
- All right. Roger.

216
00:07:33,328 --> 00:07:37,728
- OK, darling, time for this
dinosaur to head to extinction.

217
00:07:37,728 --> 00:07:39,248
- Got us through
a real jam today.

218
00:07:39,288 --> 00:07:41,408
Can't thank you enough, Monica.

219
00:07:41,448 --> 00:07:42,608
- Nice place to visit.

220
00:07:42,648 --> 00:07:44,168
Wouldn't want to live here
anymore.

221
00:07:44,168 --> 00:07:46,008
- Oh, me, neither some days.

222
00:07:46,048 --> 00:07:47,248
- But hey, Virginia Slim,

223
00:07:47,288 --> 00:07:49,248
you've come a long way.

224
00:07:49,288 --> 00:07:51,408
Glad I was wrong about you.

225
00:07:51,448 --> 00:07:52,848
Keep training 'em up right.

226
00:07:52,888 --> 00:07:54,048
- I'll try.

227
00:07:54,088 --> 00:07:55,568
- OK, that's enough mush.

228
00:07:55,608 --> 00:07:57,488
Back to my life
of mahjong and margaritas.

229
00:07:57,528 --> 00:07:59,048
Bye, Evans.
- Get home safe.

230
00:07:59,088 --> 00:08:00,688
- I will. See ya.

231
00:08:00,728 --> 00:08:01,768
- Bye.

232
00:08:05,368 --> 00:08:06,968
[sighs] She's right.

233
00:08:07,008 --> 00:08:10,288
You are the mama bear glue
that holds this place together.

234
00:08:14,608 --> 00:08:17,168
Hey, you OK?

235
00:08:17,208 --> 00:08:18,568
- No.

236
00:08:18,608 --> 00:08:21,368
I'm sad or scared,

237
00:08:21,408 --> 00:08:25,008
or some fucking thing.

238
00:08:25,008 --> 00:08:26,648
I'm worried.

239
00:08:26,648 --> 00:08:28,728
- What's going on?

240
00:08:28,768 --> 00:08:30,448
- Robby. I got a bad feeling.

241
00:08:30,448 --> 00:08:32,048
He's...

242
00:08:32,088 --> 00:08:34,128
it's like I'm never going
to see him again after tonight.

243
00:08:34,168 --> 00:08:35,408
- Did he say something?

244
00:08:35,448 --> 00:08:36,768
- Yeah,
he said a lot of things.

245
00:08:36,808 --> 00:08:38,448
You should talk to him.
He listens to you.

246
00:08:38,488 --> 00:08:39,688
- He's a grown-up.

247
00:08:39,728 --> 00:08:42,128
He just needs to go
on a vacation.

248
00:08:42,168 --> 00:08:43,808
- Can't you at least try

249
00:08:43,848 --> 00:08:46,248
to get him to promise
to come back in one piece?

250
00:08:47,768 --> 00:08:50,128
- He doesn't like to listen.

251
00:08:50,168 --> 00:08:51,808
- So make him.

252
00:08:56,568 --> 00:08:58,088
- [sighs]

253
00:08:58,128 --> 00:08:59,128
- Fuck it. Check my DMs.

254
00:08:59,168 --> 00:09:00,408
She hit me up.

255
00:09:00,448 --> 00:09:02,288
Sure, baby.
I didn't even respond.

256
00:09:02,328 --> 00:09:03,888
[siren wailing]
- Scavenger hunt?

257
00:09:03,928 --> 00:09:05,088
- Yeah, something like that.

258
00:09:05,128 --> 00:09:06,128
You need a hand?

259
00:09:06,168 --> 00:09:07,728
- Nope. You do you.

260
00:09:09,968 --> 00:09:11,008
What do we got?

261
