Okay, yes, it was a bit noisy.
The fourth is Styx night.

515
00:18:33,088 --> 00:18:34,888
But I called it.
I have witnesses.

516
00:18:34,888 --> 00:18:36,368
- Styx, the band?

517
00:18:36,408 --> 00:18:37,168
- Yeah.

518
00:18:37,208 --> 00:18:38,288
- Ah, love Styx.

519
00:18:38,328 --> 00:18:39,768
- I never heard of them.

520
00:18:39,808 --> 00:18:41,728
- You never heard of Styx?

521
00:18:41,728 --> 00:18:42,928
"Mr. Roboto"?

522
00:18:42,928 --> 00:18:45,368
- My Spotify age isn't 62.
- [sighs]

523
00:18:45,408 --> 00:18:48,088
"Come Sail Away"?
"Lady"? "Babe"?

524
00:18:48,128 --> 00:18:49,368
[groaning]

525
00:18:49,408 --> 00:18:51,728
- Yeah, maybe best
if you don't talk.

526
00:18:51,768 --> 00:18:54,648
Looks like there's some sort
of foreign body in there.

527
00:18:54,688 --> 00:18:56,168
- Mm-hmm.

528
00:18:56,208 --> 00:18:57,568
Are you OK?

529
00:18:57,608 --> 00:18:59,808
- Yeah, it's just
an awkward position.

530
00:18:59,848 --> 00:19:01,928
- Go home.
Rest, heat, ice.

531
00:19:01,968 --> 00:19:03,128
- Yeah, no, no, I know.

532
00:19:03,168 --> 00:19:04,808
I'm just waiting
for things to slow down.

533
00:19:04,848 --> 00:19:07,648
- You know, express trains
don't stop at your station.

534
00:19:08,768 --> 00:19:10,888
You just gotta jump.

535
00:19:10,888 --> 00:19:11,968
- What is that?

536
00:19:12,008 --> 00:19:13,168
Heineken?

537
00:19:13,208 --> 00:19:14,368
Moosehead?

538
00:19:14,408 --> 00:19:15,528
- Oh.

539
00:19:15,568 --> 00:19:18,288
From the glass-lined tanks
of Old Latrobe.

540
00:19:18,328 --> 00:19:20,488
- Ah, Rolling Rock.

541
00:19:20,528 --> 00:19:21,568
Nice.

542
00:19:26,008 --> 00:19:27,808
- She's had four of morphine.

543
00:19:27,848 --> 00:19:29,208
How's the pain?

544
00:19:29,208 --> 00:19:30,408
- Down to an 8.

545
00:19:30,448 --> 00:19:32,008
- There it is, lateral STEMI.

546
00:19:32,008 --> 00:19:33,208
OK, call it in.

547
00:19:33,248 --> 00:19:34,728
- The leads were too low
to catch it?

548
00:19:34,768 --> 00:19:36,368
- Yeah, it's not the first time
it's happened.

549
00:19:36,408 --> 00:19:37,808
You get a male medic
who's more concerned about

550
00:19:37,848 --> 00:19:39,448
getting sued or a complaint
for undoing a bra.

551
00:19:39,448 --> 00:19:41,008
You see these
anterior leads here?

552
00:19:41,048 --> 00:19:42,328
- Code STEMI, South 15.

553
00:19:42,368 --> 00:19:43,808
- Edith, you're having
a heart attack

554
00:19:43,848 --> 00:19:45,208
from a blockage in the artery

555
00:19:45,248 --> 00:19:46,768
that brings oxygen
to your heart muscle.

556
00:19:46,808 --> 00:19:48,928
If we get you to the--
- Lateral STEMI, V-tach arrest.

557
00:19:48,968 --> 00:19:51,128
Got her back after one shock.
She needs the cath lab.

558
00:19:51,128 --> 00:19:52,688
- And serious heart damage.
- Oh, my God.

559
00:19:52,728 --> 00:19:55,488
- You're going to be OK.
- Hello, I'm Dr. Cruz.

560
00:19:55,528 --> 00:19:57,248
- And I'm Dr. Shen.
How are you feeling?

561
00:19:57,288 --> 00:19:58,568
- I'm really scared.

562
00:19:58,608 --> 00:20:00,368
- We've got you.
Anything else?

563
00:20:00,408 --> 00:20:02,408
- Uh, like I got kicked
in the chest.

564
00:20:02,448 --> 00:20:04,208
- Normal after
a shock to the heart.

565
00:20:04,208 --> 00:20:05,808
Family?
- Yeah, husband's en route.

566
00:20:05,808 --> 00:20:07,608
- Leave the defib pads on
and take her up in a minute.

567
00:20:07,648 --> 00:20:09,088
I'm gonna chaperone
a nerve block real quick.

568
00:20:09,128 --> 00:20:10,368
- Go.

569
00:20:12,168 --> 00:20:13,888
- Where's Dr. Al-Hashimi?

570
00:20:13,928 --> 00:20:15,848
- She was just here.

571
00:20:25,128 --> 00:20:27,288
- Hello, everyone.
I'm Dr. Shen.

572
00:20:27,328 --> 00:20:29,168
Heard a rumor someone
needed a nerve block.

573
00:20:29,168 --> 00:20:30,888
I'm guessing that's you.

574
00:20:30,928 --> 00:20:32,728
- Probably so, although,

575
00:20:32,768 --> 00:20:34,408
you know,
I don't have much pain.

576
00:20:34,408 --> 00:20:36,448
I guess it's my diabetes.

577
00:20:36,488 --> 00:20:40,088
- We still need to numb you up
to do a proper deep clean.

578
00:20:40,128 --> 00:20:41,848
- You guys do
whatever you gotta do.

579
00:20:41,848 --> 00:20:44,408
- Three shots, median,
ulnar, and radial.

580
00:20:44,448 --> 00:20:46,288
2 grams of Ancef,
100 milligrams of Gent

581
00:20:46,328 --> 00:20:47,688
for gram-negative coverage.

582
00:20:47,688 --> 00:20:48,768
How'd you do this?

583
00:20:48,808 --> 00:20:51,488
- Oh, a family reunion
tug-of-war.

584
00:20:51,528 --> 00:20:53,648
I wrapped the rope around
my hand for better grip.

585
00:20:53,688 --> 00:20:56,888
And when we fell down, those
bastards just kept pulling.

586
00:20:56,928 --> 00:20:58,328
- Dirty.

587
00:20:58,328 --> 00:21:00,928
- Nah, it's just--
just the way we play.

588
00:21:00,968 --> 00:21:03,568
[laughs]

589
00:21:03,608 --> 00:21:05,168
- Michael, you got a second?

590
00:21:05,208 --> 00:21:06,648
- Uh, not really, no.

591
00:21:06,688 --> 00:21:08,688
- Well, how about
showing me a little respect

592
00:21:08,728 --> 00:21:10,808
and finding one?

593
00:21:10,848 --> 00:21:11,928
- Sorry, Caleb.

594
00:21:11,968 --> 00:21:13,328
Are you feeling disrespected?

595
00:21:13,368 --> 00:21:15,328
- Given that you've been
actively blowing me off

596
00:21:15,368 --> 00:21:17,048
all day, yeah,
maybe a little bit.

597
00:21:17,048 --> 00:21:18,608
But I have a thick skin.

598
00:21:19,848 --> 00:21:21,288
- What can I do for you?

599
00:21:21,328 --> 00:21:24,248
- "Should have found
a higher place to jump from."

600
00:21:24,288 --> 00:21:26,728
It's an interesting diagnosis,
Doctor.

601
00:21:30,688 --> 00:21:32,208
No pithy retort?

602
00:21:32,248 --> 00:21:34,248
Yeah, I didn't think so.

603
00:21:34,288 --> 00:21:36,688
Uh, I just came to say goodbye.

604
00:21:36,728 --> 00:21:38,248
I'm leaving soon.

605
00:21:38,288 --> 00:21:40,048
I know you are too.

606
00:21:41,328 --> 00:21:43,048
- Yes.

607
00:21:44,288 --> 00:21:46,528
- Keep my number handy,
just in case, huh?

608
00:21:46,568 --> 00:21:48,728
- Yes, I promise I will.

609
00:21:48,768 --> 00:21:50,008
Thank you, Caleb.

610
00:21:52,128 --> 00:21:54,528
- We're gonna give you one
Diflucan pill to take home.

611
00:21:54,568 --> 00:21:57,448
Take it in three days
if your symptoms persist.

612
00:21:57,488 --> 00:21:59,288
- How do I get there?

613
00:21:59,288 --> 00:22:00,808
- Where's that?

614
00:22:00,848 --> 00:22:02,328
- Home.

615
00:22:02,368 --> 00:22:03,568
- Do you know where you live?

616
00:22:03,608 --> 00:22:05,528
- Of course I do. It's not far.

617
00:22:05,528 --> 00:22:08,048
But I don't have
a way to get there.

618
00:22:09,168 --> 00:22:10,688
- How'd you get here?

619
00:22:10,728 --> 00:22:13,168
- My--my neighbor Gwen
dropped me off,

620
00:22:13,208 --> 00:22:15,408
but she can't drive at night.

621
00:22:15,448 --> 00:22:18,208
- We could call you
an Uber or a taxi.

622
00:22:18,208 --> 00:22:20,928
- I don't have any money.

623
00:22:20,968 --> 00:22:22,648
- Excuse me.

624
00:22:22,688 --> 00:22:24,128
Can I help?

625
00:22:24,168 --> 00:22:25,888
- Mrs. Clymer has
been discharged,

626
00:22:25,928 --> 00:22:26,888
but has no way home.

627
00:22:26,928 --> 00:22:27,928
- I'm so sorry.

628
00:22:27,968 --> 00:22:28,928
I don't mean to be a burden.

629
00:22:28,968 --> 00:22:30,248
- No burden at all.

630
00:22:30,288 --> 00:22:33,168
Why don't we call you a Lyft?

631
00:22:33,208 --> 00:22:34,448
- What is that?

632
00:22:34,488 --> 00:22:35,728
- It's like a taxi service.

633
00:22:35,728 --> 00:22:37,568
If you put your address
in here,

634
00:22:37,608 --> 00:22:40,128
a car will arrive in a few
minutes to bring you home.

635
00:22:40,168 --> 00:22:41,368
- Oh.
- My treat.

636
00:22:41,368 --> 00:22:42,568
- [laughs]

637
00:22:42,568 --> 00:22:46,808
That's very kind of you, truly.

638
00:22:46,848 --> 00:22:48,288
- Perfect.

639
00:22:48,328 --> 00:22:50,328
OK, Olive, could you take
Mrs. Clymer out

640
00:22:50,368 --> 00:22:52,888
to the ambulance bay,
where Florian will be

641
00:22:52,928 --> 00:22:55,248
arriving in six minutes
in a white Toyota Camry?

642
00:22:55,248 --> 00:22:56,408
- You bet.

643
00:22:56,448 --> 00:22:57,688
- Thank you.

644
00:22:57,728 --> 00:23:00,008
- I could use some good karma.

645
00:23:00,048 --> 00:23:01,848
OK.

646
00:23:04,488 --> 00:23:06,888
Oh, uh, hey.

647
00:23:08,328 --> 00:23:09,768
- Relax, buddy.

648
00:23:09,808 --> 00:23:11,448
It's Advil.

649
00:23:11,488 --> 00:23:13,888
- No, I didn't think you were--

650
00:23:13,928 --> 00:23:15,168
[sighs]

651
00:23:15,168 --> 00:23:16,768
Headache?

652
00:23:16,768 --> 00:23:20,008
- Uh, I tweaked my back
a little

653
00:23:20,008 --> 00:23:22,648
lifting that overheated kid.

654
00:23:22,688 --> 00:23:23,928
I guess I should get used to

655
00:23:23,968 --> 00:23:26,728
playing through the pain
again, huh?

656
00:23:26,768 --> 00:23:29,288
You look like you got into
shape since I saw you last.

657
00:23:29,328 --> 00:23:31,248
Didn't peg you as a gym guy.

658
00:23:31,288 --> 00:23:32,608
- Oh, no.

659
00:23:32,648 --> 00:23:35,448
I'm maybe more of a barn guy.
[chuckles]

660
00:23:35,488 --> 00:23:38,688
I'm helping out a friend
on the farm, so...

661
00:23:40,168 --> 00:23:41,248
- Nice.

662
00:23:41,288 --> 00:23:42,808
I'm picturing "Babe,"

663
00:23:42,848 --> 00:23:44,648
except instead of
Farmer Hoggett, it's you.

664
00:23:44,688 --> 00:23:46,128
And instead of a pig--

665
00:23:46,168 --> 00:23:48,048
- Can you cut the shit?

666
00:23:49,528 --> 00:23:50,768
- Excuse me?

667
00:23:50,808 --> 00:23:52,968
- The sarcasm thing,
the--the--the--

668
00:23:53,008 --> 00:23:54,808
the little buddy routine,
like--like--like,

669
00:23:54,808 --> 00:23:56,688
you're what, you're
the Skipper, I'm Gilligan?

670
00:23:56,728 --> 00:23:58,608
Dude, you're not the Skipper.

671
00:23:58,648 --> 00:24:00,848
- I know I'm not the Skipper.
Robby is the Skipper.

672
00:24:00,848 --> 00:24:02,928
- No, Robby is the Professor.
Dana's the Skipper.

673
00:24:02,968 --> 00:24:04,768
- OK, somebody's watched
a lot of Nick at Nite.

674
00:24:04,808 --> 00:24:07,088
So who am I?

675
00:24:07,128 --> 00:24:09,248
- Play whatever part you like.

676
00:24:09,288 --> 00:24:11,688
Just don't pick mine for me.

677
00:24:13,088 --> 00:24:14,368
- OK.

678
00:24:14,408 --> 00:24:16,408
OK, that's fair.

679
00:24:16,448 --> 00:24:18,128
You got it.

680
00:24:18,168 --> 00:24:20,328
- Thank you.

681
00:24:20,368 --> 00:24:22,648
- You headed home?

682
00:24:22,688 --> 00:24:25,448
- Uh, no, I'm waiting on Robby.

683
00:24:25,488 --> 00:24:27,088
He asked me to house-sit
while he's gone.

684
00:24:27,128 --> 00:24:30,168
So I'm waiting for the keys,
the alarm code.

685
00:24:31,448 --> 00:24:32,768
- Nice. Nice.

686
00:24:32,808 --> 00:24:34,648
Yeah, I've--
I've seen his place.

687
00:24:34,688 --> 00:24:37,088
You're in for a sweet setup.

688
00:24:37,128 --> 00:24:38,968
- Cool.

689
00:24:39,008 --> 00:24:42,848
I'm sorry if I came across
a little strong.

690
00:24:42,888 --> 00:24:45,288
- Don't apologize
for standing up for yourself.

691
00:24:45,328 --> 00:24:47,328
It's a healthy habit.

692
00:24:47,328 --> 00:24:49,088
- [sighs]

693
00:24:49,128 --> 00:24:51,168
- You know, I really don't
need to see this again.

694
00:24:51,208 --> 00:24:52,768
- No, this is my favorite part.

695
00:24:52,808 --> 00:24:54,208
[laughs]

696
00:24:54,248 --> 00:24:55,248
- My hand's starting to cramp.

697
00:24:55,288 --> 00:24:56,448
We gotta be done soon.

698
00:24:56,488 --> 00:24:58,048
- Oh, you can be done now.

699
00:24:58,088 --> 00:25:01,528
But if you want to the hospital
to cover you, last one.

700
00:25:06,808 --> 00:25:09,848
- Hey, Robby.
It was an accident, man.

701
00:25:09,888 --> 00:25:11,488
- What are you talking about?

702
00:25:11,528 --> 00:25:13,848
- Your bike.

703
00:25:17,288 --> 00:25:20,528
[sirens wailing]

704
00:25:21,528 --> 00:25:24,128
- Son of a bitch.

705
00:25:24,128 --> 00:25:26,968
Oh, motherfucker!

706
00:25:28,328 --> 00:25:30,328
- Robby, GSW to the head.

707
00:25:30,368 --> 00:25:31,568
- Somebody hit my bike.

708
00:25:31,568 --> 00:25:33,208
- Dude, that sucks.

709
00:25:33,248 --> 00:25:34,608
Is it still rideable?

710
00:25:34,648 --> 00:25:36,008
[man singing
"My Country 'Tis of Thee"]

711
00:25:36,048 --> 00:25:37,528
- It better be.

712
00:25:37,568 --> 00:25:39,728
- Elbridge Gerry, 25,
stable with good vitals.

713
00:25:39,768 --> 00:25:41,208
- ♪ Of thee I sing ♪

714
00:25:41,248 --> 00:25:42,848
- Was shooting his
.22 caliber pistol in the air

715
00:25:42,888 --> 00:25:44,448
with an aluminum pot
on his head for protection.

716
00:25:44,488 --> 00:25:45,728
Didn't work.

717
00:25:45,768 --> 00:25:47,048
- He's had about a quart
of Seagrams 7

718
00:25:47,088 --> 00:25:48,488
and will probably light up
a tox screen

719
00:25:48,488 --> 00:25:50,728
like a Roman candle.

720
00:25:50,768 --> 00:25:53,408
- ♪ We start fucking ♪

721
00:25:53,448 --> 00:25:54,768
- Real wordsmith.

722
00:25:54,808 --> 00:25:56,128
- Entry wound
in the frontal scalp,

723
00:25:56,128 --> 00:25:57,568
seems to have tracked down
the forehead.

724
00:25:57,608 --> 00:25:58,688
As alert and oriented
as you can be

725
00:25:58,728 --> 00:25:59,888
after multiple bong hits.

726
00:25:59,928 --> 00:26:01,448
Got vital satting 98
on room air.

727
00:26:01,488 --> 00:26:02,728
- Sorry, Robby.
- Don't you fucking leave.

728
00:26:02,768 --> 00:26:03,928
- I can explain.
- I will be right back.

729
00:26:03,968 --> 00:26:04,928
- What's this?

730
00:26:04,968 --> 00:26:06,288
- Trauma 2.

731
00:26:06,328 --> 00:26:07,608
- Low velocity GSW to the head,

732
00:26:07,648 --> 00:26:09,168
seems to have
remained extracranial.

733
00:26:09,208 --> 00:26:10,608
- Lucky guy.

734
00:26:10,648 --> 00:26:14,728
- ♪ Gloria, Gloria,
here's a dollar! ♪

735
00:26:14,768 --> 00:26:17,368
- After a fireworks
explosion resulting

736
00:26:17,408 --> 00:26:19,648
in the loss of two fingers.

737
00:26:19,688 --> 00:26:21,808
- Ooh, that sounds nasty.

738
00:26:21,848 --> 00:26:24,528
- Yeah, that was a sad one.

739
00:26:24,568 --> 00:26:25,848
Parents were deported.

740
00:26:25,888 --> 00:26:28,368
Big sister works
a full-time job

741
00:26:28,408 --> 00:26:29,808
and is the sole caregiver.

742
00:26:29,848 --> 00:26:31,528
- Been there, done that.

743
00:26:31,568 --> 00:26:33,368
- Your parents were deported?

744
00:26:33,408 --> 00:26:35,248
- Oh, no.
I thought she said departed.

745
00:26:36,728 --> 00:26:38,568
Did either of you guys work on

746
00:26:38,608 --> 00:26:41,248
the Revolutionary War
reenactors earlier?

747
00:26:41,288 --> 00:26:44,208
- Why, you didn't think you
could pull off a tricorn hat?

748
00:26:44,248 --> 00:26:46,928
- [chuckles]
Maybe.

749
00:26:46,968 --> 00:26:48,448
I've always loved history,

750
00:26:48,448 --> 00:26:52,648
and Colonial Williamsburg
was my favorite school trip.

751
00:26:52,688 --> 00:26:54,408
And, you know,
there's always the Ren Faire,

752
00:26:54,448 --> 00:26:56,728
but that's just once a year.

753
00:26:56,768 --> 00:26:59,208
How often do you think
the reenactors get together?

754
00:27:00,728 --> 00:27:02,528
- I don't know. No.

755
00:27:02,528 --> 00:27:04,408
- You should definitely
look into that.

756
00:27:04,448 --> 00:27:05,608
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

757
00:27:05,648 --> 00:27:07,048
- OK.

758
00:27:08,768 --> 00:27:11,968
[engine revving]

759
00:27:16,808 --> 00:27:19,168
- Deep-throated husky
with a touch of bitch.

760
00:27:19,208 --> 00:27:20,328
That's her tune.

761
00:27:20,368 --> 00:27:21,808
- That's what I thought,
but you're the expert.

762
00:27:21,848 --> 00:27:23,688
I just needed to make sure.

763
00:27:24,848 --> 00:27:26,648
- I was going through
Billings once.

764
00:27:26,688 --> 00:27:30,288
Cop saw my colors,
jacked me up,

765
00:27:30,328 --> 00:27:31,648
kept me overnight.

766
00:27:31,688 --> 00:27:35,168
They threw my sweetheart
in the impound yard.

767
00:27:35,208 --> 00:27:37,088
They claimed
someone backed into it,

768
00:27:37,128 --> 00:27:40,448
but you could see where they
took their hammer to it, man.

769
00:27:40,488 --> 00:27:41,808
You gotta be careful out there.

770
00:27:41,848 --> 00:27:43,088
- This is all pretty minor,
though, right?

771
00:27:43,128 --> 00:27:45,328
- Yeah, shit,
this is just cosmetic.

772
00:27:45,368 --> 00:27:47,928
Bring it in tomorrow,
and we'll get Bonnie right.

773
00:27:47,968 --> 00:27:49,688
- Well, this will bend back.
This will tighten up.

774
00:27:49,728 --> 00:27:51,448
I can do all that myself.
- Jesus, let me do it.

775
00:27:51,488 --> 00:27:52,648
There's no charge.
- What?

776
00:27:52,688 --> 00:27:53,968
You don't owe me anything,
except

777
00:27:54,008 --> 00:27:56,568
take care of yourself
while I'm gone.

778
00:27:56,608 --> 00:27:58,448
- Boy, this record
never stops, huh?

779
00:27:58,488 --> 00:28:01,368
- Nah, it's dance
till you drop!

780
00:28:01,408 --> 00:28:02,768
- Then what?

781
00:28:02,808 --> 00:28:05,048
- Teach the kids the steps
before you do.

782
00:28:05,088 --> 00:28:06,128
- And then what?

783
00:28:06,168 --> 00:28:07,728
- Hope they make it
farther than you.

784
00:28:07,768 --> 00:28:09,248
- Hey, Robby,
you're coming or going?

785
00:28:09,288 --> 00:28:11,088
- I'm going, pretty soon.
What have you got here?

786
00:28:11,128 --> 00:28:14,008
- Lyman Paine, 53, single MVC.

787
00:28:14,048 --> 00:28:15,368
Drove into a telephone pole.

788
00:28:15,368 --> 00:28:16,568
- Passenger space intrusion?

789
00:28:16,608 --> 00:28:17,688
- No, head on.

790
00:28:17,728 --> 00:28:18,688
- Intoxicated?

791
00:28:18,728 --> 00:28:20,648
- No ETOH on his breath.

792
00:28:20,688 --> 00:28:22,488
Either syncope, seizure,

793
00:28:22,528 --> 00:28:24,888
or he just fell asleep
at the wheel.

794
00:28:24,928 --> 00:28:26,928
Airbag deployed,
unconscious at the scene,

795
00:28:26,968 --> 00:28:28,128
but he's waking up.

796
00:28:28,168 --> 00:28:29,528
- BP 140 over 80,

797
00:28:29,568 --> 00:28:31,368
pulse 120, pulse ox 98,

798
00:28:31,408 --> 00:28:32,568
no obvious injuries.

799
00:28:32,608 --> 00:28:33,568
- Why don't you guys
head on in?

800
00:28:33,608 --> 00:28:34,928
I'll meet you in a minute.

801
00:28:39,528 --> 00:28:42,128
Well, hey, buddy,
I guess this is it.

802
00:28:42,168 --> 00:28:44,048
Make those appointments
next week, you know?

803
00:28:44,088 --> 00:28:46,128
I'll call you from the road
to make sure you do.

804
00:28:46,168 --> 00:28:47,888
- Don't do that, man.
- What?

805
00:28:47,928 --> 00:28:50,048
- Don't shine me on.

806
00:28:50,088 --> 00:28:52,008
- I'm not.

807
00:28:52,048 --> 00:28:53,368
- Jesus.

808
00:28:53,408 --> 00:28:55,008
I get it.

809
00:28:55,048 --> 00:28:58,208
Hard place to leave,
a harder place to stay.

810
00:28:59,768 --> 00:29:01,128
- Yeah.

811
00:29:03,208 --> 00:29:06,008
- Look, I'm not ready
to say goodbye yet.

812
00:29:06,048 --> 00:29:09,608
So go do what you gotta do,
and I'll get some tools

813
00:29:09,648 --> 00:29:11,888
from the truck
and see if I can't make

814
00:29:11,928 --> 00:29:14,288
Bonnie smile again for you.

815
00:29:17,768 --> 00:29:19,208
- OK.

816
00:29:19,248 --> 00:29:20,968
- OK, then.

817
00:29:27,568 --> 00:29:30,048
- Robby, man, I'm so sorry.
We've been on for 14 straight.

818
00:29:30,088 --> 00:29:31,768
I thought I cleared it.
- It's all right.

819
00:29:31,808 --> 00:29:33,008
- Honestly, I feel terrible.

820
00:29:33,008 --> 00:29:34,848
- No real harm done.

821
00:29:34,888 --> 00:29:36,688
I was bound to nick it up
on the road anyway.

822
00:29:36,728 --> 00:29:39,928
First blood drawn,
it's a good omen really.

823
00:29:39,968 --> 00:29:41,288
- Thought he'd be more pissed.

824
00:29:41,328 --> 00:29:43,528
- I thought you might
get punched.

825
00:29:43,568 --> 00:29:44,928
- Chest and belly look good.

826
00:29:44,968 --> 00:29:46,408
Let me drag Neurosurgery
down here to deal with

827
00:29:46,448 --> 00:29:47,568
the C-spine before I go.

828
00:29:47,608 --> 00:29:49,968
- You off?
- Yep, an hour ago.

829
00:29:50,008 --> 00:29:51,928
Can't you tell?
- How you doing, sir?

830
00:29:51,928 --> 00:29:54,688
- Actually, not too good.

831
00:29:54,728 --> 00:29:55,968
The tingling is getting worse.

832
00:29:55,968 --> 00:29:57,688
It's in both my arms now.

833
00:29:57,728 --> 00:29:59,168
I feel like something's wrong.

834
00:29:59,208 --> 00:30:01,368
- Hey, man.
What are we looking at?

835
00:30:01,408 --> 00:30:04,248
- Ran into a telephone pole,
airbag deployed.

836
00:30:04,288 --> 00:30:05,688
- Seizure? Stroke?

837
00:30:05,728 --> 00:30:06,968
- Not sure.

838
00:30:07,008 --> 00:30:08,088
Possible C-spine.

839
00:30:08,128 --> 00:30:10,608
CT showed
uni-facet dislocation.

840
00:30:10,648 --> 00:30:12,448
- I'm trying not to freak out.

841
00:30:12,448 --> 00:30:13,888
I'm having trouble breathing.

842
00:30:13,928 --> 00:30:16,208
- Squeeze my hand.

843
00:30:16,248 --> 00:30:17,688
Real hard.

844
00:30:17,688 --> 00:30:18,768
Three out of five strength.

845
00:30:18,808 --> 00:30:19,888
- OK.

846
00:30:19,888 --> 00:30:21,288
10 milligrams dexamethasone.

847
00:30:21,328 --> 00:30:23,368
- Dexamethasone?
For spinal injury?

848
00:30:23,408 --> 00:30:25,048
- It's compression
from a jumped facet

849
00:30:25,088 --> 00:30:26,768
and maybe some ischemia
from a kinked vessel.

850
00:30:26,808 --> 00:30:28,088
- What's--what's happening?

851
00:30:28,128 --> 00:30:30,768
- Sir, you have
a partial dislocation

852
00:30:30,768 --> 00:30:32,208
of two vertebrae in your neck.

853
00:30:32,248 --> 00:30:34,288
It's putting pressure
on your spinal cord.

854
00:30:34,328 --> 00:30:35,808
- How do you fix it?

855
00:30:35,808 --> 00:30:38,608
- We need Neurosurgery
to screw a clamp

856
00:30:38,608 --> 00:30:40,328
into both sides of your skull

857
00:30:40,368 --> 00:30:43,448
and then use traction
under X-ray guidance

858
00:30:43,448 --> 00:30:44,848
to get everything realigned.

859
00:30:44,888 --> 00:30:47,328
- Like a chiropractic
adjustment?

860
00:30:47,368 --> 00:30:50,208
- It's a bit more
complicated than that.

861
00:30:50,248 --> 00:30:52,088
- I think I'm having
a panic attack,

862
00:30:52,128 --> 00:30:55,088
because I can't even get
a shallow breath.

863
00:30:55,128 --> 00:30:57,728
- Or he's losing C3, 4, and 5.

864
00:30:57,768 --> 00:30:59,528
- Uh, page Neurosurgery.

865
00:30:59,528 --> 00:31:01,768
- Garcia went to go get them.
- No. Page overhead.

866
00:31:01,808 --> 00:31:04,328
Find Robby if he's still here.

867
00:31:04,368 --> 00:31:07,168
- Any available neurosurgeon
to ED Trauma 1, stat!

868
00:31:07,208 --> 00:31:10,608
Any available neurosurgeon
to ED Trauma 1, stat!

869
00:31:10,608 --> 00:31:12,208
[liquid trickling]

870
00:31:12,208 --> 00:31:14,368
[knocking on door]
- Dr. Robby?

871
00:31:14,408 --> 00:31:17,448
- Uh, yeah?

872
00:31:17,488 --> 00:31:20,568
[toilet flushes]
- You're needed in Trauma 1.

873
00:31:20,608 --> 00:31:22,208
- OK.

874
00:31:22,248 --> 00:31:23,688
What patient?
- Dr. Langdon's.

875
00:31:23,728 --> 00:31:25,168
It's a neck injury.

876
00:31:28,088 --> 00:31:29,248
- I got the fellow.

877
00:31:29,288 --> 00:31:30,728
They could be down
in 15 minutes.

878
00:31:30,728 --> 00:31:31,928
- He's progressing
too fast for that.

879
00:31:31,928 --> 00:31:33,848
- What's going on?

880
00:31:33,888 --> 00:31:36,288
- Uni-facet dislocation, C4/C5,

881
00:31:36,328 --> 00:31:38,288
paresthesia
and decreased tidal volume.

882
00:31:38,328 --> 00:31:39,368
- Sat's 85.

883
00:31:39,368 --> 00:31:41,328
- We need to prepare
for intubation.

884
00:31:41,368 --> 00:31:43,088
- Any delay in reduction
almost guarantees

885
00:31:43,128 --> 00:31:45,368
complete spinal cord injury.

886
00:31:45,408 --> 00:31:47,368
- What other options
do we have?

887
00:31:47,408 --> 00:31:51,088
- Uh, I saw Neurosurgery do
a closed reduction once in ICU.

888
00:31:51,128 --> 00:31:52,648
- Blind? That's crazy risky.

889
00:31:52,688 --> 00:31:53,888
- We gotta do something.

890
00:31:53,928 --> 00:31:55,368
What's that procedure,
Dr. Langdon?

891
00:31:55,408 --> 00:31:57,488
- It's just--
it's traction on the neck,

892
00:31:57,528 --> 00:32:00,248
we flex the dislocated side
and into slight extension.

893
00:32:00,288 --> 00:32:01,608
- Quadriplegia, if done wrong.

894
00:32:01,648 --> 00:32:03,528
- I'm sorry, what--
did you say quadriplegic?

895
00:32:03,528 --> 00:32:04,928
- It is a possibility, sir.

896
00:32:04,928 --> 00:32:06,768
It's also the same possibility
if we do nothing.

897
00:32:06,808 --> 00:32:07,968
- You wanna try?

898
00:32:08,008 --> 00:32:09,808
- I've never seen it done.
You have.

899
00:32:09,848 --> 00:32:11,168
- I can't feel my feet.

900
00:32:11,208 --> 00:32:12,808
- Sats 79. 100% non-rebreather?

901
00:32:12,848 --> 00:32:14,088
- He's progressing,
Dr. Langdon.

902
00:32:14,128 --> 00:32:15,648
What is your plan?

903
00:32:15,688 --> 00:32:17,048
- Uh, Neuro--

904
00:32:17,088 --> 00:32:18,608
- Fuck Neuro.
This is right here, right now.

905
00:32:18,608 --> 00:32:20,288
This guy's gonna be
a living head if we do nothing.

906
00:32:20,328 --> 00:32:23,048
- I could paralyze him.
- Doctor the fuck up.

907
00:32:23,048 --> 00:32:24,848
[machine beeping]

908
00:32:24,888 --> 00:32:27,248
- [gasping]

909
00:32:27,288 --> 00:32:30,128
- Sir, the partial dislocation
of the two vertebrae

910
00:32:30,168 --> 00:32:32,408
in your neck is putting
pressure on your spinal cord.

911
00:32:32,448 --> 00:32:35,128
I can try to move the neck
bones back into place.

912
00:32:35,128 --> 00:32:37,088
That could help.
There's no guarantees.

913
00:32:37,128 --> 00:32:38,528
If we do nothing,

914
00:32:38,528 --> 00:32:40,248
the weakness is definitely
going to get worse.

915
00:32:40,288 --> 00:32:42,848
But either way, there's still
a chance of paralysis.

916
00:32:42,888 --> 00:32:45,528
- Do it.
Please. Please.

917
00:32:45,568 --> 00:32:47,008
- 50 of fentanyl IV.

918
00:32:47,048 --> 00:32:48,648
You need to let us know
if the weakness gets worse

919
00:32:48,688 --> 00:32:51,088
or if there's any sudden pain,
and we'll stop immediately.

920
00:32:51,128 --> 00:32:52,528
Dr. Cruz, Robby,

921
00:32:52,568 --> 00:32:55,008
hold down his shoulders
for countertraction.

922
00:32:55,048 --> 00:32:56,968
OK, I'm gonna pull
on your head.

923
00:32:57,008 --> 00:32:58,928
Your job is to try to relax,

924
00:32:58,968 --> 00:33:01,488
breathe so we can overcome
the muscle spasm.

925
00:33:01,488 --> 00:33:04,408
[machine beeping]

926
00:33:06,208 --> 00:33:08,048
Flexing to the right.

927
00:33:11,008 --> 00:33:12,208
Any change?

928
00:33:12,248 --> 00:33:14,728
- My legs are starting
to tingle.

929
00:33:14,768 --> 00:33:16,408
- Last step.

930
00:33:19,208 --> 00:33:20,608
[bones crack]
- Ah!

931
00:33:20,608 --> 00:33:21,968
- I felt something click.
- Oh, fuck! Oh, fuck!

932
00:33:22,008 --> 00:33:23,608
- I felt it too.
- Sir, talk to us.

933
00:33:23,648 --> 00:33:25,128
What's going on?
- Oh.

934
00:33:25,168 --> 00:33:27,168
[panting]
I think--

935
00:33:27,208 --> 00:33:28,488
I think...
[laughs]

936
00:33:28,528 --> 00:33:30,768
Yeah.
I'm starting to breathe easier.

937
00:33:30,808 --> 00:33:32,848
- Any change
in your hand or feet?

938
00:33:32,888 --> 00:33:34,288
- Oh.

939
00:33:34,288 --> 00:33:35,768
Oh, this is maybe
a little less numb.

940
00:33:35,808 --> 00:33:37,448
- Philadelphia collar is ready.

941
00:33:37,488 --> 00:33:38,568
- Talk to me.

942
00:33:38,608 --> 00:33:39,808
- Langdon just reduced

943
00:33:39,848 --> 00:33:41,488
a uni-facet
cervical dislocation.

944
00:33:41,528 --> 00:33:44,328
- What? Without neurosurgery?
Don't try this at home, kids.

945
00:33:44,328 --> 00:33:45,968
- He was deteriorating quickly.

946
00:33:46,008 --> 00:33:47,368
- Neuro exam is improving.

947
00:33:47,368 --> 00:33:49,568
- Oh, my God,
it's definitely better.

948
00:33:49,608 --> 00:33:52,448
Oh, my God.

949
00:33:52,488 --> 00:33:54,128
- Nice job.

950
00:33:54,168 --> 00:33:55,488
- All right, repeat CT,

951
00:33:55,528 --> 00:33:57,088
then Neurosurgery
can take him up for a halo.

952
00:33:57,128 --> 00:33:58,368
Brass balls, buddy.

953
00:33:58,408 --> 00:34:00,448
See? You haven't lost it.
- Um, excuse me.

954
00:34:00,488 --> 00:34:03,288
I'm just gonna step outside
for a second.

955
00:34:17,848 --> 00:34:20,848
- Langdon, honey, I just got
a call from upstairs.

956
00:34:20,888 --> 00:34:22,168
Were you supposed to get
a urine screen

957
00:34:22,208 --> 00:34:23,928
and turn it in by 8:00 tonight?
- Fuck!

958
00:34:23,968 --> 00:34:25,288
Um...

959
00:34:26,248 --> 00:34:28,448
Oh, no.
Uh, ye--yes.

960
00:34:28,488 --> 00:34:30,648
Can you just--can you tell them
that I was in a trauma?

961
00:34:30,688 --> 00:34:32,168
I'm going right now.

962
00:34:35,768 --> 00:34:37,368
- Where's he off to?

963
00:34:37,408 --> 00:34:39,008
- No idea.

964
00:34:39,048 --> 00:34:41,448
Did you find your ID badge yet?

965
00:34:41,488 --> 00:34:43,448
- No, I've looked everywhere.

966
00:34:43,488 --> 00:34:45,168
Must have been thrown out
on accident.

967
00:34:45,208 --> 00:34:46,568
- They'll issue you a new one.

968
00:34:46,608 --> 00:34:48,008
You just have to fill out
a bunch of forms.

969
00:34:48,048 --> 00:34:49,568
[notification chimes]
- Oh, great.

970
00:34:53,528 --> 00:34:54,928
What?

971
00:34:54,968 --> 00:34:55,928
- Cow in labor?

972
00:34:55,968 --> 00:34:57,288
- No, I--

973
00:34:57,328 --> 00:34:59,008
I ordered a patient a Lyft.

974
00:34:59,048 --> 00:35:03,808
Now I have a $250 surcharge
and a complaint on my account.

975
00:35:03,808 --> 00:35:05,888
- What?
- What'd they do?

976
00:35:05,928 --> 00:35:07,248
- It was a sweet old lady.

977
00:35:07,248 --> 00:35:09,288
- Who apparently had
some racist

978
00:35:09,328 --> 00:35:11,008
and abusive things to say

979
00:35:11,048 --> 00:35:13,248
right before puking
in the back.

980
00:35:13,248 --> 00:35:16,008
- You never know
with some people.

981
00:35:16,048 --> 00:35:17,288
- There goes my first paycheck.

982
00:35:17,328 --> 00:35:18,888
- St. Huckleberry.

983
00:35:18,888 --> 00:35:20,288
No good deed.

984
00:35:23,088 --> 00:35:26,128
- I can see why you liked
restoring this bike.

985
00:35:26,128 --> 00:35:27,888
You're a fixer.

986
00:35:27,928 --> 00:35:29,968
I fix bikes,
but you fix people.

987
00:35:30,008 --> 00:35:32,528
That's pretty damn
impressive, man.

988
00:35:32,568 --> 00:35:34,768
- Some people can't be fixed.

989
00:35:36,088 --> 00:35:38,248
- Look, I'm--

990
00:35:38,288 --> 00:35:41,248
I've done plenty of things
I'm not proud of.

991
00:35:41,288 --> 00:35:42,248
- Yeah, me too.

992
00:35:42,288 --> 00:35:45,008
- No, bad things--

993
00:35:45,048 --> 00:35:47,688
hurt people on purpose,

994
00:35:47,688 --> 00:35:49,288
hurt myself.

995
00:35:49,328 --> 00:35:52,328
And I did my time, but that
doesn't wash away the regret.

996
00:35:52,368 --> 00:35:54,448
I...

997
00:35:54,488 --> 00:35:56,888
wish I'd done things
differently.

998
00:35:56,928 --> 00:35:59,248
I think about it every day.

999
00:35:59,288 --> 00:36:02,368
- You know, they say that
it's never too late to change.

1000
00:36:02,408 --> 00:36:06,168
- Some things can't be changed,
like death.

1001
00:36:06,168 --> 00:36:08,008
Death can't be changed.

1002
00:36:08,048 --> 00:36:09,968
- Hey, I know
the surgery is scary.

1003
00:36:10,008 --> 00:36:12,728
- I'm not talking about me.

1004
00:36:26,328 --> 00:36:29,608
- Yeah, I don't know if
I wanna be here anymore.

1005
00:36:31,408 --> 00:36:33,888
- I don't know how you stand
12 minutes in there,

1006
00:36:33,928 --> 00:36:38,568
let alone 12 hours, 20 years.

1007
00:36:38,608 --> 00:36:39,608
- No.

1008
00:36:39,648 --> 00:36:41,928
That's the only place I can be.

1009
00:36:41,968 --> 00:36:47,288
I have purpose in there.
I can be distracted in there.

1010
00:36:47,328 --> 00:36:51,088
I don't know that I wanna be...

1011
00:36:51,128 --> 00:36:55,048
anywhere anymore.

1012
00:36:55,088 --> 00:36:57,288
[exhales]

1013
00:37:00,008 --> 00:37:02,328
- So what's the plan?

1014
00:37:02,368 --> 00:37:05,048
[distant sirens wailing]
- Ride.

1015
00:37:05,088 --> 00:37:06,928
- Toward what?
- I don't know.

1016
00:37:06,968 --> 00:37:08,048
- Away from what?

1017
00:37:08,088 --> 00:37:09,808
- Everything.

1018
00:37:09,848 --> 00:37:13,168
- Well, that's not riding.
That's running.

1019
00:37:13,208 --> 00:37:16,488
Is that your final lesson
for these kids?

1020
00:37:21,408 --> 00:37:22,808
- What's up, Robby?

1021
00:37:22,848 --> 00:37:26,768
- Well, if it isn't
Medics Bosco and Otero.

1022
00:37:28,888 --> 00:37:29,928
- You still on?

1023
00:37:29,968 --> 00:37:31,088
- Not for much longer.

1024
00:37:31,128 --> 00:37:33,368
I was looking for you two.

1025
00:37:33,408 --> 00:37:34,928
- Rita Wolcott, 22.

1026
00:37:34,928 --> 00:37:37,288
She was using a dumpster
to climb a fire escape

1027
00:37:37,328 --> 00:37:38,688
to get to a roof party.

1028
00:37:38,728 --> 00:37:40,528
Slipped about 6 feet
onto concrete.

1029
00:37:40,568 --> 00:37:42,248
Possible tib-fib fracture.

1030
00:37:42,288 --> 00:37:43,568
- Oh, can I please tell it?

1031
00:37:43,568 --> 00:37:45,168
You're making me sound
like an idiot.

1032
00:37:45,168 --> 00:37:47,048
My friends and I were just
trying to watch the fireworks

1033
00:37:47,088 --> 00:37:48,408
from the roof of our building.

1034
00:37:48,448 --> 00:37:50,568
But the roof access door
and the stairwells stuck,

1035
00:37:50,608 --> 00:37:52,768
so we decided to climb
the fire escape.

1036
00:37:52,808 --> 00:37:54,968
They were supposed to hold
the dumpster still while I...

1037
00:37:55,728 --> 00:37:56,808
But they didn't.

1038
00:37:56,848 --> 00:37:58,088
Then I fell.

1039
00:37:58,128 --> 00:38:00,248
- Like I said,
6 feet onto concrete.

1040
00:38:00,248 --> 00:38:02,048
- Yeah, because they didn't
hold it still.

1041
00:38:02,088 --> 00:38:03,888
- Well, it's a good thing
she didn't need a 12-lead.

1042
00:38:03,928 --> 00:38:05,488
- Why's that?

1043
00:38:05,528 --> 00:38:06,968
- 'Cause you guys put one on
about a half hour ago wrong

1044
00:38:07,008 --> 00:38:08,128
and you missed the STEMI.

1045
00:38:08,168 --> 00:38:09,128
- Bullshit.

1046
00:38:09,168 --> 00:38:10,288
- 46-year-old woman.

1047
00:38:10,328 --> 00:38:12,128
A minute after you left,
V-tach.

1048
00:38:12,128 --> 00:38:14,608
Repeat EKG showed
a massive lateral STEMI.

1049
00:38:14,648 --> 00:38:15,568
- No way.

1050
00:38:15,608 --> 00:38:16,968
- Leads were so inferior,

1051
00:38:16,968 --> 00:38:18,648
you might as well
have not put them on at all.

1052
00:38:18,688 --> 00:38:20,288
What were you afraid of,
her bra?

1053
00:38:20,328 --> 00:38:21,688
- What have we got?

1054
00:38:21,728 --> 00:38:23,968
- We've got a 22-year-old
probable tib-fib fracture

1055
00:38:24,008 --> 00:38:25,208
from a 6-foot fall.

1056
00:38:25,248 --> 00:38:26,888
Why don't you take her
to Central 13?

1057
00:38:26,928 --> 00:38:28,248
- Got it. Right this way.

1058
00:38:28,248 --> 00:38:29,968
- As I was saying,
bad data is shit data.

1059
00:38:30,008 --> 00:38:32,448
- Maybe she was diaphoretic
and they slid down en route.

1060
00:38:32,448 --> 00:38:33,808
- Yeah, she was moving a lot.

1061
00:38:33,848 --> 00:38:35,368
- Diaphoretic, my ass.
She had big breasts.

1062
00:38:35,408 --> 00:38:36,688
You didn't wanna move 'em
out of the way

1063
00:38:36,728 --> 00:38:38,448
to get under her bra line.
- Come on, Robby.

1064
00:38:38,488 --> 00:38:39,968
- Women are misdiagnosed
for heart attacks all the time.

1065
00:38:40,008 --> 00:38:41,288
This is a big reason why.

1066
00:38:41,328 --> 00:38:42,568
Shall we put it to a vote?

1067
00:38:42,608 --> 00:38:44,888
Hey, ladies in the room,
show of hands.

1068
00:38:44,928 --> 00:38:47,448
Death with modesty,
or life with brief nudity?

1069
00:38:47,488 --> 00:38:49,928
Death or life?

1070
00:38:49,968 --> 00:38:51,968
Look at that--
turns out women wanna live.

1071
00:38:51,968 --> 00:38:53,288
- Got it.

1072
00:38:53,328 --> 00:38:54,488
- EKG is an amazing tool
if you use it right.

1073
00:38:54,528 --> 00:38:55,808
- You could have told us
in private.

1074
00:38:55,808 --> 00:38:57,288
- I think this was
more instructive.

1075
00:38:57,328 --> 00:38:59,128
- Agreed.

1076
00:39:00,568 --> 00:39:03,048
- Hey, hell of a save
your boy made.

1077
00:39:03,088 --> 00:39:04,328
On-the-fly reduction

1078
00:39:04,368 --> 00:39:06,208
of a uni-facet
cervical dislocation--

1079
00:39:06,248 --> 00:39:07,448
that's some cowboy shit.

1080
00:39:07,488 --> 00:39:08,928
- Yeah, it was.
Where is he?

1081
00:39:08,968 --> 00:39:10,608
- Ran off for a drug test.

1082
00:39:10,648 --> 00:39:13,048
You got your wish.
You don't have to say goodbye.

1083
00:39:18,648 --> 00:39:21,408
- Hey, thank you
for saying all that.

1084
00:39:21,448 --> 00:39:23,768
I may have taken a slightly
different approach, but--

1085
00:39:23,768 --> 00:39:25,248
- I seem to have lost
my filter.

1086
00:39:25,288 --> 00:39:26,648
- I'm glad.

1087
00:39:26,688 --> 00:39:29,288
I could use an honest
second opinion on a case.

1088
00:39:29,328 --> 00:39:31,768
Do you have five minutes
to spare?

1089
00:39:33,008 --> 00:39:34,848
- Sure. Why not?

1090
00:39:34,848 --> 00:39:35,888
What's the case?

1091
00:39:35,928 --> 00:39:38,008
- I have the chart
pulled up in 8.

1092
00:39:50,128 --> 00:39:51,168
[beep]

1093
00:39:52,688 --> 00:39:54,608
I have some experience
with this,

1094
00:39:54,648 --> 00:39:56,728
but I'd appreciate
a fresh perspective.

1095
00:39:56,768 --> 00:39:58,808
- [chuckles]
After 14 hours,

1096
00:39:58,848 --> 00:40:00,448
I don't know how fresh
my perspective is,

1097
00:40:00,488 --> 00:40:02,008
but I will give you what I got.

1098
00:40:02,008 --> 00:40:04,568
- Well, after working with you,
Dr. Robinavitch,

1099
00:40:04,608 --> 00:40:08,008
I've come to respect
your opinion.

1100
00:40:10,128 --> 00:40:12,448
- Thank you, Dr. Al-Hashimi.

1101
00:40:14,168 --> 00:40:16,128
Likewise.

1102
00:40:16,168 --> 00:40:18,888
OK, patient is a 40-year-old
female with a history

1103
00:40:18,928 --> 00:40:20,808
of seizure disorder
for the past 35 years.

1104
00:40:20,848 --> 00:40:22,488
She had no perinatal
complications

1105
00:40:22,528 --> 00:40:24,408
and was in excellent health
until age five,

1106
00:40:24,448 --> 00:40:26,048
when she had
the onset seizure activity

1107
00:40:26,088 --> 00:40:28,688
following prolonged illness
with viral meningitis.

1108
00:40:28,728 --> 00:40:31,928
Her altered mental status
from the infec...

1109
00:40:39,608 --> 00:40:42,648
Baran, is this you?
